---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About - May">
  <section class="page-header">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="content narrow">
    <p class="lead">
      I'm May. I write about what I'm figuring out.
    </p>

    <p>
      I've worked in strategy, product, and operations. I've lived in different cities.
      I left relationships that no longer fit. I changed careers more than once.
      I lost people. I started over. And in each transition, I developed a way of thinking
      that helped me - and started helping the people around me.
    </p>

    <p>
      I combined mathematical modeling with five years in HR. Entrepreneurship with therapy.
      Grief with curiosity. Depression with frameworks. And I realized that the combination
      of human depth and strategic intelligence is rare - and useful.
    </p>

    <div class="divider" style="margin: 3rem auto;"></div>

    <h2>What I believe</h2>

    <ul class="beliefs">
      <li>That clarity doesn't come from having more information, but from separating signal from noise.</li>
      <li>That most hard decisions aren't about logic - they're about identity.</li>
      <li>That you don't need to figure out your whole life at once. You need the next truest step.</li>
      <li>That fear isn't a sign that something is wrong. Sometimes it's a sign that something important is close.</li>
      <li>That thinking better is a skill - and it can be trained.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider" style="margin: 3rem auto;"></div>

    <h2>This space</h2>

    <p>
      Welcome to my little corner of the internet - part library, part lab,
      part journal. A place where I organize the frameworks, mental models,
      and questions that help me (and maybe you) think with more clarity
      about what actually matters.
    </p>

    <p>
      Everything here comes from real life - career changes, grief, starting
      over, figuring out what kind of life I actually want. AI has been helping
      me plot my brain and map how I think. Not theory. Practice.
    </p>

    <p class="closing">
      If something here helps you think more clearly about a hard decision,
      then this site has served its purpose.
    </p>

    <div class="divider" style="margin: 3rem auto;"></div>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>

    <p>
      <a href="mailto:hello@mayra.villas">hello@mayra.villas</a><br>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/mayravillasboas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 5rem auto 3rem;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.4rem;
  }

  .content {
    padding: 0 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 6rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .beliefs {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .beliefs li {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .beliefs li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }

  .closing {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
